sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J07036
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Threshold: Repression module (cI repressor with junk region)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Part of the thresholding device (works with j07037, j07038/j07039/j07040). This encodes the cI repressor that normally represses j07037. However, j07038/39/40 code for antisense mRNA to this, which, when transcribed, represses translation of cI and activates j07037
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yaser (Ray) Khan

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I1030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RNA Regulation Target ( Promoter driven by C0040 and cI mod #1 CDS)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the tetR promoter (<bb_part>BBa_C0040</bb_part>) with antisense binding region for <bb_part>BBa_I1031</bb_part> and <bb_part>BBa_I1032</bb_part>, and a codon modified cI(1) protein with an LVA degradation tail.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Neelaksh Varshney, Samantha Sutton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
BBa_I1030 Custom cI Protein with TetR Promoter is based on BioBricks BBa_C0050 and BBa_R0040. It is designed such that BBa_I1031 and BBa_I1032can be used to interfere with the BBa_1030 transcript by anti-sense mRNA binding, in the KISS or micRNA method shown below. BBa_I1030 and BBa_I1031 or BBa_I1032 can act indepently of related biobrick parts BBa_I1041, BBa_I1042, BBa_I1020, BBa_BBa_I1023 and BBa_1013. [KEIL96]

Incompatible with systems containing IPTG, or cI.

May be some cross talk with systems containing BBa_I1010. Compatible with all other BBa_line I-line parts.

Proper operation requires AMP/CAP complex, which should normally be present in the cell.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
